  "commentary": "With SPX at 6596.16 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-29.8B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+29.2B), dealers are caught in a precarious hedging zone where they're forced to buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any rally toward 6605. The BREAKOUT regime with -38.7B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, creating a volatile 15-point corridor where hedging flows will be intense. Watch 6590 as the critical support where dealer buying should emerge, while 6605 becomes the key resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings between 6590 and 6605 with dealers pushing price around like a pinball.",
